public static enum ModelUpdate.PersonUpdaterFn extends Enum<ModelUpdate.PersonUpdaterFn>
Person-level updaters: run for every person during the updateState phase (see Updater.updateState(Person)). These get access to the person's next-state builder and the current person object so they can make deterministic or probabilistic modifications to the next state before it is finalised.

  • Enum Constant Details

    • DEFAULT

      public static final ModelUpdate.PersonUpdaterFn DEFAULT
      Default no-op person updater. This exists so the Updater has at least one person processor by default and demonstrates the expected lambda shape.

    • IMMUNISATION_PROTOCOL

      public static final ModelUpdate.PersonUpdaterFn IMMUNISATION_PROTOCOL
      Immunisation (vaccination) protocol placeholder.

      Current behaviour: sets the next state's immunisation dose to 0.0 as a placeholder. Intended use:

      1. Be extended to consult outbreak-level vaccine supply and prioritisation.
      2. Apply doses to eligible individuals by mutating the next-state builder (e.g. builder.setImmunisationDose(...)) and schedule follow-up doses.
      3. Interact with the in-host model and risk model so that vaccination affects susceptibility, severity and waning parameters.
      Important: the full vaccination workflow (eligibility, queueing, multi-dose schedules and waning immunity) is not implemented here. Treat this enum value as a scaffolding point for productionising vaccine logic; prefer implementing a dedicated person processor or service that can be added via Updater.withPersonProcessor(java.util.function.Predicate, io.github.ai4ci.flow.mechanics.ModelOperation.TriConsumer) when building an experiment.

    • IMPORTATION_PROTOCOL

      public static final ModelUpdate.PersonUpdaterFn IMPORTATION_PROTOCOL
      Importation protocol: demonstrates how one might seed exposure on the next day using a per-person probability scaled by model parameters and the agent's mobility. This adds an importation exposure to the next state builder if the random draw succeeds; otherwise it leaves the importation exposure as zero.
